The paper addresses the problem of cross-referencing text fragments with Wikipedia pages, which is a common task in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed system, TAGME, uses machine learning techniques to perform entity linking, which falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The system also involves working with large amounts of data, which could be stored in databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper presents experimental results that compare TAGME to other state-of-the-art algorithms, which is a common practice in machine learning (cs.LG).
